			<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
			<h3>Statement from the Board of Directors</h3>
			<!-- /wp:heading -->

			<!-- wp:paragraph -->
			<p>Racism, bias, and inequity for Black, Indigenous, and people of color (BIPOC) plagues communities and reaches deep to all aspects of society, including ocean sciences and conservation. Our core mission at the Cordell Marine Sanctuary Foundation (CMSF) involves supporting science &amp; education at Cordell Bank National Marine Sanctuary (CBNMS) to better understand the past, present, and future of the unique and special place that is CBNMS. This understanding is directly related to climate change and the health of our planet and its inhabitants. Systemic oppression, climate change and environmental protection are deeply intertwined; and disproportionately and drastically affect BIPOC communities, locally and around the world. CMSF stands in solidarity with Black Lives Matter, and all those protesting racial injustice. We commit to doing our part to dismantle white supremacy and to help build a more diverse and inclusive science, education, and conservation program at CBNMS. We call for a future that puts the needs of justice and community first.</p>
			<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
		</div>
		<!-- /wp:column -->

